article.headline: Niagara 78, Duquesne 74
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- J.R. Duffey had a double-double, finishing with 17 points and 11 rebounds, to lead Niagara to a 78-74 win over visiting Duquesne in a non-conference game Saturday. Clif Brown had 20 points for the Purple Eagles (2-6), who posted their first home victory in five attempts this season. Tyrone Lewis had 16 points and Stanley Hodge came off the bench to hand out a career-high 10 assists. Robert Mitchell had a game-high 26 points for the Dukes (2-7), who have lost seven straight after opening the year with two wins. Kieron Achara had 17 points and Aaron Jackson added 13 for Duquesne. Duquesne, which trailed by as many as 12 points in the second half, had a chance to tie it in the final seconds, but Jackson missed a layup with six seconds remaining. Brown then hit two free throws with 4.7 seconds to seal the win for Niagara.
